abstract: As he runs for president, Joseph R. Biden Jr. has trumpeted his ability to work with Republicans, including Mitch McConnell. Others in his party view that as antiquated and unrealistic.
snippet: As he runs for president, Joseph R. Biden Jr. has trumpeted his ability to work with Republicans, including Mitch McConnell. Others in his party view that as antiquated and unrealistic.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Mitch McConnell, the Senate Republican leader and self-described “grim reaper” of liberal legislative dreams, settled into a routine of sorts during Barack Obama’s second term whenever he felt he was cornered by Democrats.

abstract: All the highlights from the spring 2020 shows, as captured by T’s photographers.
snippet: All the highlights from the spring 2020 shows, as captured by T’s photographers.
lead_paragraph: Richard Quinn has a knack for staging theatrical shows, and his latest outing closed London Fashion Week with a definitive bang. The designer enlisted London’s Philharmonic Orchestra and the Bach Choir to perform live inside East London’s York Hall, where models paraded across a bubble-gum-pink carpet in big, bold, after-dark dresses. There were polka-dot puffball looks, exaggerated leg-of-mutton satin sleeves, latex bodysuits under cheongsam-style dresses and, of course, the designer’s signature screen-printed florals in long columnar shapes. The supermodel Jacquetta Wheeler led a bevy of feathered schoolgirls across the floor to close the show, swiftly followed by the unveiling of a tableau vivant of Quinn’s bridal collection against a backdrop of foliage. Unsurprisingly, the audience went wild.

abstract: They have staked out diverging political paths, but have mostly refrained from attacking each other. Now a more combative phase of the race seems inevitable.
snippet: They have staked out diverging political paths, but have mostly refrained from attacking each other. Now a more combative phase of the race seems inevitable.
lead_paragraph: If Joseph R. Biden Jr. and Elizabeth Warren are headed for a showdown, neither of them appears in a hurry to get there.

abstract: The Democratic National Committee has announced that the next debate will be held on Oct. 15, with a possible second night on Oct. 16.
snippet: The Democratic National Committee has announced that the next debate will be held on Oct. 15, with a possible second night on Oct. 16.
lead_paragraph: The New York Times and CNN will co-host the next Democratic debate near Columbus, Ohio, on Oct. 15, with the possibility of a second round one night later depending on how many candidates meet the qualifying criteria.

abstract: There is little evidence that stays by military personnel at President Trump’s resort in Scotland are part of a scheme to enrich him. But they have raised ethical and political questions.

snippet: With an assist from the internet, politicians have become pop icons, and citizens their fans. What does that mean for our politics?
lead_paragraph: Whatever persona Elizabeth Warren hopes to project in her presidential campaign, it is probably not that of a child witch. But that is the persona that some of her biggest fans have chosen for her.
